        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 8 at 2:44PM EDT by NWS Wilmington NC</headline>
        <description>At 243 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
White Stocking, or near Burgaw, moving northeast at 45 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Burgaw, White Stocking, Murray Town, Maple Hill, St. Helena, and
Pender Memorial Hospital.

This includes Interstate 40 between mile markers 396 and 403.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 500 PM EDT for
southeastern North Carolina.</instruction>
